title: SCARY STORIES TO TELL IN THE DARK Ending + Monsters Explained!
author: Think Story
comment: I'm pretty new to doing these videos from movies just released in theaters so I have to use clips from the trailers and online featurettes. Hope you like these types of vids!
If there is a sequel, I hope my boy Auggie is rescued.

Something that is ironic is how Auggie is always talking to his friends about not eating something because of “How many body parts are in it” or “How it can cause infertility” yet in his story he eats a stew with several body parts in it.
Who Else Is Still Waiting For James To Make A Kill Count? Just Me?

This movie did exactly what it was supposed to. It was no masterpiece but it was well acted, the effects were nice and blended well, and the subject matter was just dark enough to make it ok for kids to watch.
description:
We take a deep dive into the Guillermo Del Toro written horror film "Scary Stories to Tell in the Dark" explaining its ending and reviewing its many creepy monsters.
